"Pours a medium brown color, slight chill haze.  The aroma is full of cinnamon rolls, sweetness, vanilla and malts.  The taste has some sweetness, slight buttery character, ginger, cinnamon, allspice, and breads.  Sweet and spices work surprisingly well with a brown ale base and Shipyard's temperamental yeast strain,  Drinks easy enough and has that holiday spice many are seeking,  This is a pretty interesting beer from Shipyard."
