"Bottle. Pours a clear, copper color. Mild head. Looks very light bodied. Aroma is packed with gingerbread. It's completely dedicated to smell like gingerbread. It smells so convincingly on-point I am sure it's jam-packed with artificial flavoring. The flavor is much the same. Gingerbread and accompanying spices. Light bodied. Zesty bubbles. Lingering flavor. Too much flavoring, needs more beer characteristics."
